comments: Smith Jr. (HOU) moves alongside Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the driving shot attempt.
Sengun (HOU) lowers his left arm down and makes contact with Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) arm, which affects his layup attempt at the basket.
Roddy (MEM) and Sengun (HOU) come together off-ball and the contact is marginal.
Sengun (HOU) steps out into Williams Jr.'s (MEM) path and delivers leg contact that delays him from defending around the pick.

As Smith Jr. (HOU) reaches in and makes marginal contact with Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) front, Jackson Jr. leans his head into Smith Jr.'s arm.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Sengun (HOU) avoids making contact with Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) arm during his legal contest of the driving shot attempt.
Smith Jr. (HOU) moves alongside Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the driving shot attempt.
Bane (MEM) turns and initiates body contact with VanVleet (HOU) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Williams Jr. (MEM) steps into VanVleet's (HOU) path and lower body contact occurs that affects VanVleet's SQBR during the drive.
Sengun (HOU) and Williams Jr. (MEM) jostle for position in the paint and the contact is marginal.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes himself in Eason's (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact when setting the screen.

VanVleet (HOU) lowers his hand down to the ball and makes contact with the ball and incidental hand on ball contact with Williams Jr. (MEM), which legally dislodges the ball during the jump shot attempt.
VanVleet (HOU) makes last contact with the ball prior to it going out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Memphis.
Brooks (HOU) is moving alongside Bane's (MEM) path and marginal body contact occurs during Bane's drive.
Roddy's (MEM) left hand brushes Brooks' (HOU) side during the drive into the frontcourt and the contact is marginal.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) jumps towards Eason (HOU) and makes contact with the ball and incidental contact with his hand on the ball.  The ensuing body contact is incidental, as well.
Brooks (HOU) lowers his arm down as he jumps into the air and marginal contact occurs with Williams Jr.'s (MEM) shoulder during the rebounding opportunity.

Brooks (HOU) brings his right arm toward the ball and marginal brush contact occurs with the side of Roddy's (MEM) head during the rebounding opportunity. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
VanVleet (HOU) brings his hand toward the ball and legally brushes it after Jackson Jr. (MEM) gathers the ball and comes to a stop.
Roddy (MEM) reaches for the ball and makes illegal contact with the back of Smith Jr.'s (HOU) head.
Smith Jr. (HOU) makes last contact with the ball prior to it falling out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Memphis.
